{'content_type': 'audio_transcription', 'text': 'Yeah, absolutely. Major historical traumas like the Black Plague and World War II had profound impacts on collective worldviews. After such cataclysmic events, people often question established beliefs and search for new ways to make sense of the world. The existential crises triggered by these events led to a rise in skepticism about absolute truths and grand narratives, fostering movements like postmodernism and a more subjective understanding of values.

